        {
            "blockname": "Pre-Placement",
            "name": "The Equality Act",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "What is it?",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The Equality Act was introduced to simplify and strengthen discrimination laws across Britain. It harmonised 116 pieces of legislation. The aim of the legislation is to protect certain categories of people from unfair treatment.",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "What is a disability under the Equality Act",
                            "type": "video-single",
                            "video": {
                                "type": "youtube",
                                "src": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/NRtztkc35hg",
                                "thumb": "equality_act_disability.jpg"
                            },
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Protected Characteristics",
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Age"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Disability"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Gender reassignment"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Marriage and civil partnership"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Race"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Religion or belief"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Sex"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Sexual Orientation"
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Key Issues",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Direct discrimination",
                            "type": "text-quote",
                            "text": "An individual or organisation that provides services to the public must not treat someone worse just because of one or more protected characteristics…",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Indirect discrimination",
                            "type": "text-quote",
                            "text": "An organisation must not do something to someone in a way that has a worse impact on them and other people who share a particular protected characteristic than it has on people who do not share that characteristic. Unless the organisation can show that what they have done is objectively justified…",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Discrimination arising from disability",
                            "type": "text-quote",
                            "text": "Service providers must not treat disabled people unfavourably because of something connected to their disability where they cannot show that what they are doing is objectively justified. This only applies if the individual or organisation knows, or could reasonably have been expected to know, that the person is disabled",
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Summary",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "A good summary of the Equality Act can be found at the link below: ",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "link-website",
                            "links": [
                                {
                                    "tag": "",
                                    "text": "Summary of the Equality Act",
                                    "link": "https://www.equalityhumanrights.com/sites/default/files/equality_act_summary_guidance_on_services.pdf"
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The Equality Act allows for discrimination against any of the protected characteristics.",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-quote",
                            "text": "The Equality Act says discrimination can be justified if the person who's discriminating against you can show it’s a proportionate means of achieving a legitimate aim. If necessary, it's the courts which will decide if discrimination can be justified",
                            "author": "Citizen’s advice website",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-quote",
                            "text": "A legitimate aim is the reason behind the discrimination. This reason must not be discriminatory in itself and it must be a genuine or real reason.",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Here are some examples of legitimate aims: ",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "the health, safety and welfare of individuals"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "running an efficient service"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "requirements of a business"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "desire to make profit"
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Health and social care training programmes need to ensure that potential registrants are capable of meeting the competencies set out in the regulatory guidelines and can support the delivery of an efficient service.",
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Understanding the Act",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The following link points to a document that contains valuable information regarding the understanding of the Equality Act.",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "link-website",
                            "links": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Understanding the Equality Act",
                                    "link": "https://www.disabilityrightsuk.org/understanding-equality-act-information-disabled-students?platform=hootsuite"
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-mythfact",
                            "myths": [
                                {
                                    "myth": "Once an employer has hired a disabled person, they can’t sack them.",
                                    "fact": "An employer can dismiss a disabled employee if the dismissal is justified and they have taken all the correct steps."
                                },
                                {
                                    "myth": "Nobody thinks in stereotypes – we’re more sophisticated now.",
                                    "fact": "In 2015, it was reported that 42% of disabled people seeking work found the biggest barrier to getting hired were misconceptions around what they could do."
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": false
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "blockname": "Pre-Placement",
            "name": "Reasonable Adjustments",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "subtitle": "Why reasonable adjustments?",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Equality law identifies disabled people as one of eight protected categories in society. This means that the way society organises education, employment and access to recreation, etc. needs to be restructured to account for any barriers that may treat people with disabilities unfairly. In higher education, the law states it is the duty of institutions to provide students with disabilities reasonable adjustments.",
                            "space_after": true
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "What is it?",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "Reasonable adjustments are very simply any alterations that need to be made to ensure a disabled person is not disadvantaged. However, the changes have to be considered reasonable. There are certain considerations that could be made when deciding if something is “reasonable”: ",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "For example: ",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "list-text",
                            "list_elements": [
                                {
                                    "text": "How effective the change will be in avoiding the disadvantage the disabled worker would otherwise experience"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Its practicality"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Its cost"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Your organisation’s resources and size"
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "The availability of financial support.(GOV.UK website)",
                                    "links": [
                                        {
                                            "portion": "GOV.UK",
                                            "href": "https://www.gov.uk/recruitment-disabled-people/reasonable-adjustments"
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "What Reasonable Adjustments to expect?",
                    "components": [
                        {
                            "subtitle": "",
                            "type": "text-paragraph",
                            "text": "The link below will take you to the Disability Rights website which has a very detailed list of all the reasonable adjustments you should expect from employers.",
                            "space_after": false
                        },
                        {
                            "subtitle": "Link: ",
                            "type": "link-website",
                            "links": [
                                {
                                    "text": "Disability Rights UK",
                                    "link": "https://www.disabilityrightsuk.org/adjustments-disabled-students"
                                }
                            ],
                            "space_after": false
                        }
                    ],
                    "space_after": true
                },
                {
                    "subtitle": "Videos on Reasonable Adjustments",
                    "components": [
                        {
